  "text": "Gaussian blob model Explicit computation of scattering coefficients for general signals is difficult because a modulus is a non-linear operator that usually leads to non-analytic expressions. Therefore, we consider a simplified class of signals [CITATION_1] for which computations are exact and analytical. For a symmetric matrix \u03a3, we consider the unnormalized signal Figure 2 , which are frequent in natural images [CITATION_2] . We apply our reconstruction algorithm and we explain why the reconstructions is challenging.",
